<title type="html"><![CDATA[can the RP2C02G PPU be reversed engineered?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=154&amp;p=967#p967"><![CDATA[
Yeah, it can (and has) been reverse engineered almost completely.  It's been on-going for a while, and there's still new things being discovered about it.<br /><br />I know someone who's implemented the 2C02 in an Altera FPGA and I've seen it work (perfectly, as far as I could tell), so it definitely can be simulated.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Sat Jan 22, 2005 10:55 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
